column5: Howcumzit that folks who got here way after some of us have a single or a double digit member number while we gets a number in the hundreds? And some of the prilileged low digits don't hardly even fish! LOL!  Something we missed... a payment or membership of some kind?
Yah gotta hang with the right people to get the first 10 Chris ! LOL

Cisco, when we all migrated here, we had a choice, start anew with post count, or have our existing post count(if we could remember it, or if the old board was still relatively available to confirm it) and have one of the mods reset our post count to reflect what it was before the new board. Lots of us, including yours truly, chose to have our existing post count from the old board matched to this new board. NO membership required, just ask a mod to reset your post count to what you think, or know, what it was before the new board software change.
I did that Tsja. My post count reflectsthe fact I only comment when I have something to say.... whad'd ya say Wayne...
it's not who you know it's who you ... wait what's my number...hmmmmm must be just luck

The member numbers were assigned to the person in the order that they joined the new board.Some of the low number guys were helping test the new board for a couple of days before it went online.Mostly it was the guys that dont fish much that had the time to help test the board. Joe
Both Plummas always usually come out with correct and logical answers.
"Its not who ya know..."  yes it is.. lol..  and fir $1000 you can have any number you want... except Waynes.. no one can afford that..
Yeah .. thats what it was ..  ... I was outta town for a few days
Stocks eh.... hmmmm... how much would I have to pay to have someone take this off my hands... lol
I will start the bidding at 1,000.00 $ US to take it off your hands anyone in for less?  Art
